00:07:24.777 --> 00:07:29.073
<i>♪ The wild night is callin'</i>... ♪

103
00:07:31.325 --> 00:07:34.328
<i>(Song continues playing)</i>

104
00:07:35.204 --> 00:07:37.123
<i>(Horn honks)</i>

105
00:07:37.206 --> 00:07:39.458
<i>♪ All the girls walk by... ♪</i>

106
00:07:40.334 --> 00:07:41.544
- <i>(Thelma)</i> Hey.
- Hey.

107
00:07:41.627 --> 00:07:43.129
<i>(Song fades)</i>

108
00:07:44.046 --> 00:07:47.425
No, Thelma, we don't need the lantern.
The place has electricity.

109
00:07:47.508 --> 00:07:49.343
Oh. Okay. No, I want to take it anyway.

110
00:07:49.427 --> 00:07:50.970
- Just in case.
- In case of what?

111
00:07:51.053 --> 00:07:54.015
In case there's some escaped
psycho killer on the loose

112
00:07:54.098 --> 00:07:58.519
who cuts the electricity off
and tries to come in and kill us.

113
00:07:58.603 --> 00:08:01.939
Sure, Thelma. Well, then
that lantern'll come in real handy.

114
00:08:03.065 --> 00:08:05.151
Maybe we should
just tow your car behind too

115
00:08:05.234 --> 00:08:07.028
in case he steals the spark plugs.

116
00:08:07.111 --> 00:08:09.488
We'd have to. That thing barely makes it
down the driveway.

117
00:08:09.572 --> 00:08:10.948
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

118
00:08:18.497 --> 00:08:19.498
<i>(Garage door closes)</i>

119
00:08:24.337 --> 00:08:26.339
<i>("House of Hope" playing)</i>

120
00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:29.759
- Careful. Careful.
- Okay.

121
00:08:30.635 --> 00:08:32.928
- All right. Everything in?
- Yeah.

122
00:08:33.012 --> 00:08:34.597
Careful. Here you go.

123
00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:36.641
- <i>(Exclaims)</i> Be careful!
- All right.

124
00:08:38.267 --> 00:08:39.268
Smile.

125
00:08:40.728 --> 00:08:41.896
<i>(Both)</i> Whoo!

126
00:08:41.979 --> 00:08:43.981
<i>(Louise)</i> Yeah! See you later!

127
00:08:46.359 --> 00:08:47.568
Sit down!

128
00:08:47.652 --> 00:08:49.278
<i>("House of Hope" continues playing)</i>

129
00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:51.280
- Oh, Louise?
- Uh-huh?

130
00:08:51.364 --> 00:08:54.450
- Will you take care of this gun?
- What in hell did you bring that for?

131
00:08:54.533 --> 00:08:58.037
Oh, come on.
Psycho killers or bears or snakes.

132
00:08:58.120 --> 00:08:59.914
I just don't know how to use it.
Will you take care of it?

133
00:08:59.997 --> 00:09:02.667
Put it awa...
Just... Here. Put it in my purse.

134
00:09:03.668 --> 00:09:05.294
Thelma, good Lord.

135
00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:10.132
<i>♪ I don't like where we're going
I don't like it, no... ♪</i>

136
00:09:10.216 --> 00:09:15.221
- So whose place is this again?
- It's Bob's, the day manager's.

137
00:09:15.304 --> 00:09:17.056
He's gettin' a divorce.
His wife's gettin' this place.

138
00:09:17.139 --> 00:09:20.893
So he's lettin' all his friends use it
till he's gotta turn over the keys.

139
00:09:20.976 --> 00:09:23.813
<i>♪ If we don't show them how... ♪</i>

140
00:09:23.896 --> 00:09:26.524
I've never been out of town
without Darryl.

141
00:09:26.607 --> 00:09:28.317
How come Darryl let you go?

142
00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:31.278
'Cause I didn't ask him.

143
00:09:31.362 --> 00:09:33.030
Shit, Thelma.

144
00:09:33.114 --> 00:09:36.158
Why... <i>(Laughs)</i> He's gon' kill you!

145
00:09:36.242 --> 00:09:38.661
- <i>(Laughing)</i>
- Well, he'd never let me go.

146
00:09:38.744 --> 00:09:42.206
He never lets me do one goddamn thing
that's any fun.

147
00:09:42.289 --> 00:09:45.167
All he wants me to do is
hang around the house the whole time

148
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:46.961
while he's out doing God only knows what.

149
00:09:47.962 --> 00:09:49.839
Well, you get what you settle for.

150
00:09:51.048 --> 00:09:54.009
- I left him a note.
- <i>(Laughs)</i>

151
00:09:54.093 --> 00:09:57.513
- I left him stuff to microwave.
- <i>(Cackles)</i>

152
00:09:57.596 --> 00:10:00.516
<i>♪ Children laugh, children cry ♪</i>

153
00:10:00.599 --> 00:10:03.310
<i>♪ They're the ones who will survive ♪</i>

154
00:10:03.394 --> 00:10:06.355
<i>♪ Will they know what we've sold? ♪</i>

155
00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:09.233
<i>♪ Nature's gift we turn for gold ♪</i>

156
00:10:09.316 --> 00:10:14.989
<i>♪ I don't like what I see now in my life
What I see now ♪</i>

157
00:10:15.072 --> 00:10:18.033
<i>♪ I don't like where we're goin' ♪</i>

158
00:10:18.117 --> 00:10:20.911
<i>♪ I don't like it, no... ♪</i>

159
00:10:20.995 --> 00:10:22.538
- Thelma.
- What?

160
00:10:24.373 --> 00:10:25.958
<i>(Both chuckle)</i>

161
00:10:27.626 --> 00:10:29.670
<i>♪ You and I ♪</i>

162
00:10:29.754 --> 00:10:34.467
<i>♪ Who will show them
If we don't show them how? ♪</i>

163
00:10:34.550 --> 00:10:38.429
<i>♪ I wanna know, is it true? ♪</i>

164
00:10:38.512 --> 00:10:42.349
<i>♪ Is there a house of hope ♪</i>

165
00:10:42.433 --> 00:10:44.643
<i>♪ For me and you? ♪</i>

166
00:10:44.727 --> 00:10:47.104
- Thelma, what are you doin'?
- Smoking.

167
00:10:47.188 --> 00:10:50.149
<i>♪ I wanna know, is it true? ♪</i>

168
00:10:50.232 --> 00:10:52.109
Hey. I'm Louise.

169
00:10:52.193 --> 00:10:54.195
<i>♪ Is there a house of hope ♪</i>

170
00:10:54.278 --> 00:10:56.155
<i>♪ For me and you? ♪</i>

171
00:10:58.532 --> 00:11:01.911
I'll never make it.
Can't we just stop somewhere for a minute?

172
00:11:01.994 --> 00:11:05.080
Thelma, we're not gonna get to the cabin
till after dark as it is.

173
00:11:05.164 --> 00:11:07.541
Then what difference would it make
if we stopped?

174
00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:10.127
Come on.
I never get to do stuff like this.

175
00:11:10.211 --> 00:11:13.589
- Okay. But it's gonna be a quick stop.
- Fine. Okay.

176
00:11:18.302 --> 00:11:19.720
<i>(Thelma screams)</i>

177
00:11:31.899 --> 00:11:34.109
<i>("I Don't Want to Love You <i>(But I Do)</i>"
playing)</i>

178
00:11:34.193 --> 00:11:36.695
<i>♪ Take me into town, baby, for a date ♪</i>

179
00:11:39.323 --> 00:11:44.620
<i>♪ Well, I'm still waitin' here
And it's half past two... ♪</i>

180
00:11:44.703 --> 00:11:46.789
<i>(Customers chattering)</i>

181
00:11:46.872 --> 00:11:52.169
<i>♪ And I don't wanna love you
But I do ♪</i>

182
00:11:52.253 --> 00:11:54.588
I haven't seen a place like this
since I left Texas.

183
00:11:54.672 --> 00:11:55.923
Isn't this fun?

184
00:11:56.006 --> 00:12:00.928
<i>♪ When you took me to that place
With a little dance floor ♪</i>

185
00:12:02.596 --> 00:12:07.142
<i>♪ You said you'd never been
In there before ♪</i>

186
00:12:07.226 --> 00:12:09.353
<i>(Song continues playing)</i>

187
00:12:09.436 --> 00:12:12.064
- Y'all want a drink?
- Um, no, thanks.

188
00:12:12.147 --> 00:12:15.234
I'll have a Wild Turkey straight up
and a Coke back, please.

189
00:12:15.317 --> 00:12:16.819
Thelma!

190
00:12:16.902 --> 00:12:19.864
Oh, what? Tell me something.
Is this my vacation or isn't it?

191
00:12:19.947 --> 00:12:22.533
I mean, God, you're as bad as Darryl.

192
00:12:22.616 --> 00:12:25.327
I'm sorry. It's just I'm not used to
seeing you this way.

193
00:12:25.411 --> 00:12:28.956
I haven't seen you this way in a while.
You're usually so sedate.

194
00:12:29.665 --> 00:12:31.834
Well, I've had it up to my ass
with sedate.

195
00:12:31.917 --> 00:12:32.877
<i>(Louise laughs)</i>

196
00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:34.545
You said you and me
was gonna get out of town

197
00:12:34.628 --> 00:12:37.047
and, for once,
just really let our hair down.

198
00:12:37.131 --> 00:12:40.718
Well, darlin', look out,
'cause my hair is coming down.

199
00:12:40.801 --> 00:12:42.761
All right. I've changed my mind.

200
00:12:42.845 --> 00:12:47.391
I'm gonna have a margarita
and a shot of Cuervo on the side.

201
00:12:48.058 --> 00:12:49.602
- Okay.
- All right! Get me another one.

202
00:12:49.685 --> 00:12:53.188
<i>♪ I don't wanna love you, but I do ♪</i>

203
00:12:53.272 --> 00:12:54.857
<i>(Customer)</i> Hey.

204
00:12:54.940 --> 00:12:58.694
Now, what are a couple of Kewpie dolls
like you doin' in a place like this?

205
00:12:58.777 --> 00:13:01.405
- We left town for the weekend...
- Minding our business. Why don't you try?

206
00:13:01.488 --> 00:13:02.489
...to have some fun.

207
00:13:02.573 --> 00:13:06.118
And 'cause Louise here is mad
at her boyfriend 'cause...

208
00:13:07.578 --> 00:13:11.081
- We just wanted to get something to eat.
- Well, you've come to the right place.

209
00:13:11.165 --> 00:13:13.584
Do you like chili? They got good chili.

210
00:13:14.376 --> 00:13:17.212
Harlan, you botherin' these poor girls?

211
00:13:17.296 --> 00:13:19.214
Hell, no. I was just bein' friendly.

212
00:13:19.298 --> 00:13:22.593
Well, it's a good thing
they're not all as friendly as you.

213
00:13:23.302 --> 00:13:26.805
Hey, your name's Harlan?
I got an uncle named Harlan.

214
00:13:26.889 --> 00:13:28.015
- You do?
- Uh-huh.

215
00:13:28.098 --> 00:13:29.600
Is he a funny uncle?

216
00:13:29.683 --> 00:13:32.728
'Cause if he is,
then he and I got something in common.

217
00:13:32.811 --> 00:13:34.438
<i>(Both chuckling)</i>

218
00:13:36.941 --> 00:13:38.901
I don't mean to be rude,

219
00:13:38.984 --> 00:13:42.029
but I got something I got
to talk to my friend about in private.

220
00:13:42.696 --> 00:13:45.115
I... I understand.
I didn't mean to bother you.

221
00:13:45.199 --> 00:13:49.328
It's just hard not to notice
two such pretty ladies as yourselves.

222
00:13:51.538 --> 00:13:56.085
You better dance with me before you leave,
or I will never forgive you.

223
00:13:56.168 --> 00:13:57.962
- Sure, that'd be fun.
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>

224
00:14:01.590 --> 00:14:03.926
Geez, Louise. That wasn't very nice.

225
00:14:04.009 --> 00:14:06.136
Can't you tell
when somebody's hittin' on you?

226
00:14:06.220 --> 00:14:08.389
Oh, so what if he was?

227
