00:27:45.371 --> 00:27:48.082
It's a nightclub, Hal, not a drive-in.

456
00:27:48.166 --> 00:27:50.835
I don't follow the customers
out to the parking lot.

457
00:27:50.919 --> 00:27:52.212
- <i>(Chuckles)</i> All right.
- All right.

458
00:27:52.295 --> 00:27:54.547
- Lena, go on home.
- Oh!

459
00:27:54.631 --> 00:27:55.924
You kept me here all night

460
00:27:56.007 --> 00:27:58.635
to ask me the same old question
over and over again?

461
00:27:58.718 --> 00:28:00.386
<i>(Hal laughs)</i>

462
00:28:00.470 --> 00:28:03.890
Ain't you gonna offer me some teeny-eeny,
witty-bitty little drink?

463
00:28:04.808 --> 00:28:07.185
- Behave yourself.
- Oh!

464
00:28:08.394 --> 00:28:11.773
Neither of those two
was the murdering type, Hal.

465
00:28:11.856 --> 00:28:13.233
<i>(Engine starts)</i>

466
00:28:13.316 --> 00:28:15.193
<i>(Siren wailing)</i>

467
00:28:15.944 --> 00:28:17.529
<i>(Coin clatters in phone)</i>

468
00:28:17.612 --> 00:28:19.906
<i>(Line ringing)</i>

469
00:28:19.989 --> 00:28:22.242
<i>(Voice mail)</i> <i>Uh, hi, this is Jimmy.</i>

470
00:28:22.325 --> 00:28:23.368
<i>(Coin drops)</i>

471
00:28:31.543 --> 00:28:33.253
- <i>(Water running)</i>
- Thelma, you in there?

472
00:28:33.336 --> 00:28:34.587
<i>(Thelma)</i> Uh-huh.

473
00:28:44.848 --> 00:28:47.308
Thelma, come on.
We're out of here, Thelma! Come on.

474
00:28:47.392 --> 00:28:49.644
<i>(Toilet flushes)</i>

475
00:28:50.562 --> 00:28:55.233
<i>(Radio announcer)</i> <i>The Dow Jones dropped
over 12points today, closing at 18...</i>

476
00:28:56.609 --> 00:28:57.944
We're gonna need money.

477
00:28:59.112 --> 00:29:00.613
Thelma, how much money you have on you?

478
00:29:01.948 --> 00:29:02.949
What?

479
00:29:04.701 --> 00:29:07.662
I'm gonna stop at the next town.
We'll get a motel room.

480
00:29:07.745 --> 00:29:10.498
I can rest for a little bit
and then I'll figure out what to do.

481
00:29:10.582 --> 00:29:13.459
Okay. Wait. I'm looking.

482
00:29:13.543 --> 00:29:15.378
<i>(Radio announcer continues)</i>

483
00:29:17.964 --> 00:29:19.257
Sixty-one dollars.

484
00:29:20.717 --> 00:29:21.926
Shit.

485
00:29:24.178 --> 00:29:25.597
Forty-one dollars.

486
00:29:27.640 --> 00:29:29.058
We're gonna need more money.

487
00:29:30.059 --> 00:29:32.645
What are you doing? Why are you unpacking?

488
00:29:33.980 --> 00:29:35.565
You said we was just gonna take a nap.

489
00:29:35.648 --> 00:29:38.359
Well, I'm trying to figure out what to do.

490
00:29:40.778 --> 00:29:41.863
Well...

491
00:29:43.489 --> 00:29:46.492
when you figure it out, just wake me up.

492
00:29:49.329 --> 00:29:51.331
What the hell's wrong with you?

493
00:29:51.414 --> 00:29:53.291
<i>(Exhales)</i> What's that supposed to mean?

494
00:29:53.374 --> 00:29:56.711
- I mean, why are you acting like this?
- Acting like what?

495
00:29:56.794 --> 00:29:58.671
How am I supposed to act?

496
00:29:58.755 --> 00:30:02.091
Excuse me for not knowin' how to act
when you blow somebody away!

497
00:30:02.175 --> 00:30:04.218
You could help me try
to figure out what to do.

498
00:30:04.302 --> 00:30:07.096
I'm trying to figure out what to do.
But you could try...

499
00:30:07.180 --> 00:30:10.767
Try? I did! I had a suggestion
that we go to the police.

500
00:30:10.850 --> 00:30:13.686
But you didn't like that,
so frankly, Louise, I'm out of ideas.

501
00:30:13.770 --> 00:30:15.229
Well, what's the big rush, Thelma?

502
00:30:15.313 --> 00:30:18.316
I mean, we give 'em enough time
they'll come to us.

503
00:30:22.570 --> 00:30:24.530
<i>(Thelma sobbing)</i>

504
00:30:31.204 --> 00:30:33.581
Shh, shh, shh. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

505
00:30:33.665 --> 00:30:36.459
I'm just not ready to go to jail yet,
okay?

506
00:30:40.296 --> 00:30:42.382
Uh, why don't you, um...

507
00:30:43.633 --> 00:30:46.844
Why don't you go out to the pool
and take a swim or something, all right?

508
00:30:47.845 --> 00:30:49.514
Now, I'll figure out what to do.

509
00:30:51.349 --> 00:30:52.350
<i>(Phone line beeps)</i>

510
00:30:52.433 --> 00:30:54.978
Jimmy, this is Louise.
Look, I've been trying to call you.

511
00:30:55.061 --> 00:30:58.272
- <i>(Jimmy)</i> <i>Louise? Hey, baby.</i>
- Hey.

512
00:30:59.065 --> 00:31:01.401
<i>Now, where the hell are you at?</i>

513
00:31:01.484 --> 00:31:04.195
<i>- Are you all right?</i>
- Yeah, I'm fine. How are you?

514
00:31:04.278 --> 00:31:06.489
Uh, long time no see.

515
00:31:06.572 --> 00:31:10.743
<i>- You sound kind of funny, Louise.</i>
- I am funny. I'm real funny.

516
00:31:10.827 --> 00:31:13.329
<i>Are you in town? It sounds long-distance.</i>

517
00:31:14.580 --> 00:31:16.791
No, I'm out of town. I'm in, uh...

518
00:31:18.960 --> 00:31:21.087
I'm in deep shit, Jimmy.
Deep Shit, Arkansas.

519
00:31:22.880 --> 00:31:26.426
Louise, now you just tell me
what the hell's going on here.

520
00:31:27.427 --> 00:31:29.929
I come back, nobody knows where you are.

521
00:31:31.264 --> 00:31:33.558
- Is Thelma with you?
<i>- Listen, Jimmy.</i>

522
00:31:35.018 --> 00:31:37.395
I have about $6,700 in the bank.

523
00:31:37.478 --> 00:31:39.522
Now, I know you can't get it out...

524
00:31:41.024 --> 00:31:42.525
but I need that money.

525
00:31:43.985 --> 00:31:47.697
Can you wire me the $6,700
and I'll pay you back?

526
00:31:47.780 --> 00:31:50.283
What the fuck is going on here, Louise?

527
00:31:50.992 --> 00:31:52.410
Listen, uh...

528
00:31:54.328 --> 00:31:56.330
Something real bad has happened.

529
00:31:58.750 --> 00:32:00.501
And I can't tell you what.

530
00:32:02.754 --> 00:32:07.133
Just that I did it and I can't undo it.

531
00:32:10.261 --> 00:32:12.764
<i>Will you help me, please?</i>

532
00:32:12.847 --> 00:32:15.433
Yeah, yeah, yeah, baby, of course I can.

533
00:32:16.601 --> 00:32:18.853
<i>- But where? Why can't I bring it to you?</i>
- <i>(Cries)</i>

534
00:32:21.230 --> 00:32:23.232
<i>(Louise gasping)</i>

535
00:32:27.153 --> 00:32:28.154
Jimmy.

536
00:32:32.366 --> 00:32:33.826
Do you love me?

537
00:32:33.910 --> 00:32:35.745
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

538
00:32:39.248 --> 00:32:40.875
<i>(Sighs)</i> <i>Yeah.</i>

539
00:32:40.958 --> 00:32:43.169
- Never mind. Never mind. Never mind.
<i>- Yeah, yeah.</i>

540
00:32:43.252 --> 00:32:44.670
Look, just, uh...

541
00:32:46.422 --> 00:32:50.134
Just wire it to Western Union
in, uh, Oklahoma City, okay?

542
00:32:50.218 --> 00:32:52.220
<i>Oh, so that's where you're at.
Oklahoma, huh?</i>

543
00:32:52.303 --> 00:32:53.304
Not yet.

544
00:32:53.387 --> 00:32:56.474
You call me back
and I'll tell you which office to go to.

545
00:32:56.557 --> 00:33:00.770
All right. All right.
You call... I'll call you back in an hour.

546
00:33:00.853 --> 00:33:04.190
- <i>("Part of Me, Part of You" playing)</i>
- <i>(Horn honks)</i>

547
00:33:04.273 --> 00:33:05.483
Thelma!

548
00:33:05.566 --> 00:33:11.489
<i>♪ I can feel it
When I hear that lonesome highway ♪</i>

549
00:33:13.491 --> 00:33:14.408
Thelma!

550
00:33:14.492 --> 00:33:17.203
<i>♪ So many miles to go before I die... ♪</i>

551
00:33:17.286 --> 00:33:18.704
- Thelma! Thelma!
- <i>(Both scream)</i>

552
00:33:18.788 --> 00:33:20.248
- What?
- Get in the car.

553
00:33:20.331 --> 00:33:21.249
Okay.

554
00:33:21.332 --> 00:33:26.045
<i>♪ We can never know about tomorrow ♪</i>

555
00:33:28.714 --> 00:33:33.219
<i>♪ Still we have to choose
Which way to go ♪</i>

556
00:33:36.389 --> 00:33:41.561
<i>♪ You and I are standing
At the crossroads ♪</i>

557
00:33:41.644 --> 00:33:45.148
Even if they didn't do it, it times out
they most likely witnessed it,

558
00:33:45.231 --> 00:33:46.732
so somebody better talk to them.

559
00:33:46.816 --> 00:33:49.694
Put out an APB and see what we get back.

560
00:33:49.777 --> 00:33:51.362
All right.

561
00:33:51.445 --> 00:33:53.614
Any reason to believe
they've left the state?

562
00:33:56.242 --> 00:33:57.618
That's certainly possible.

563
00:33:57.702 --> 00:34:01.122
<i>Well, why don't we go ahead
and let the Bureau in on this?</i>

564
00:34:11.632 --> 00:34:16.470
Louise, don't get mad, okay,
but where are we going?

565
00:34:16.554 --> 00:34:18.222
Oklahoma City.

566
00:34:18.306 --> 00:34:20.266
Jimmy's gonna wire me some money
and then we're gonna...

567
00:34:20.349 --> 00:34:21.225
Jimmy?

568
00:34:21.309 --> 00:34:24.228
You talked to him? Did you tell him?
What did he say? Is he mad?

569
00:34:24.312 --> 00:34:26.564
No, I didn't tell him.
That's what we gotta get straight.

570
00:34:26.647 --> 00:34:30.193
Darryl's been calling, mad as a hornet,
making all kinds of noise.

571
00:34:31.027 --> 00:34:32.820
And when you call him,

572
00:34:32.904 --> 00:34:35.364
you gotta not tell him anything
about this.

573
00:34:35.448 --> 00:34:37.450
You gotta just make sure
everything sounds real normal.

574
00:34:38.242 --> 00:34:41.204
You know, I called the asshole
at four o'clock in the morning.

575
00:34:41.287 --> 00:34:42.580
He wasn't even home.

576
00:34:43.331 --> 00:34:45.541
I don't know what he's got
to be mad about.

577
00:34:45.625 --> 00:34:47.585
I'm the one that should be mad.

578
00:34:50.379 --> 00:34:51.547
Thelma.

579
00:34:53.090 --> 00:34:54.508
I'm going to Mexico.

580
00:34:54.592 --> 00:34:57.220
Now, I figure I can make it
in two and a half days,

581
00:34:57.303 --> 00:34:59.263
but I'm gonna have to haul ass.

582
00:35:00.306 --> 00:35:01.807
Are you up to this?

583
00:35:01.891 --> 00:35:04.393
I mean, I gotta know. This isn't a game.

584
00:35:05.269 --> 00:35:08.064
I'm in deep shit,
and I gotta know what you're gonna do.

585
00:35:10.900 --> 00:35:13.819
I don't know. I don't know, Louise.

586
00:35:13.903 --> 00:35:16.030
I mean, uh,
I don't know what you're asking.

587
00:35:16.113 --> 00:35:19.116
Now, don't you start flaking out on me!
Goddamn it, Thelma.

588
00:35:19.200 --> 00:35:20.826
Every time that we get in trouble,

589
00:35:20.910 --> 00:35:25.790
you just get blank or... or...
or plead insanity or some such shit.

590
00:35:25.873 --> 00:35:29.335
Not this time.
I mean, this time things have changed.

591
00:35:29.418 --> 00:35:30.878
Everything's changed.

592
00:35:34.799 --> 00:35:36.509
But I'm goin' to Mexico.

593
00:35:37.635 --> 00:35:39.011
I'm goin'.

594
00:36:03.160 --> 00:36:05.162
<i>(Coins clattering in phone)</i>

595
00:36:08.791 --> 00:36:10.501
<i>(Number pad clicking)</i>

596
00:36:15.756 --> 00:36:18.259
<i>(Line ringing)</i>

597
00:36:18.342 --> 00:36:19.385
- <i>(Phone rings)</i>
- Louise?

598
00:36:19.468 --> 00:36:22.054
<i>- Is that the way you answer the phone?</i>
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>

599
00:36:22.138 --> 00:36:23.889
I was afraid I missed you.

600
00:36:24.890 --> 00:36:26.851
I, uh... I... I got it.

601
00:36:26.934 --> 00:36:29.103
I was afraid I couldn't get a check cashed
on Saturday.

602
00:36:29.186 --> 00:36:30.396
Who did it?

603
00:36:31.397 --> 00:36:33.274
<i>A friend of mine who owns a club.
Doug Randall.</i>

604
00:36:33.357 --> 00:36:36.527
- You didn't tell him what for, did you?
- No, I didn't say what it was for.

605
00:36:36.610 --> 00:36:39.113
- I told him I was buyin' a car.
- Good. That's real good.

606
00:36:39.196 --> 00:36:41.282
Listen, uh, where do I go?

607
00:36:41.365 --> 00:36:43.576
It's a place called the Vagabond Motel.

608
00:36:44.910 --> 00:36:48.164
It's at 1921 North East 23rd.

609
00:36:48.998 --> 00:36:50.916
It's under "Peaches."

610
00:36:51.000 --> 00:36:53.711
What? <i>(Chuckles)</i>

611
00:36:54.628 --> 00:36:55.963
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

612
00:36:56.047 --> 00:36:58.090
That's the code word.

613
00:36:58.174 --> 00:36:59.884
I miss you, Peaches.

614
00:36:59.967 --> 00:37:02.928
Thanks, Jimmy. I appreciate it.

615
00:37:15.191 --> 00:37:18.819
Ma'am, you sure you wouldn't rather
have a large, economy size?

616
00:37:21.489 --> 00:37:22.948
No, no, that's okay.

617
00:37:25.242 --> 00:37:26.994
What are you lookin' at?

618
00:37:27.078 --> 00:37:28.371
- Hey.
- Hey.

619
00:37:28.454 --> 00:37:30.373
I want you to call Darryl.

620
00:37:30.456 --> 00:37:31.874
- Call him?
- Mm-hmm.

621
00:37:31.957 --> 00:37:35.544
Tell him you're having a wonderful time
and you'll be home tomorrow night.

622
00:37:35.628 --> 00:37:37.963
- Will I be?
- I don't know.

623
00:37:38.756 --> 00:37:39.757
I won't.

624
00:37:41.884 --> 00:37:43.886
Ah! The newspaper.

625
00:37:46.931 --> 00:37:48.265
<i>(Crowd cheering on TV)</i>

626
00:37:48.349 --> 00:37:51.519
<i>(Announcer chattering on TV)</i>

627
00:37:51.602 --> 00:37:54.146
<i>And Witherspoon had a great play.
Watch this right here.</i>

628
00:37:54.230 --> 00:37:56.232
<i>(Phone rings)</i>

629
00:37:58.651 --> 00:37:59.652
This is Darryl.

630
00:37:59.735 --> 00:38:03.197
<i>(Operator)</i> <i>I have a collect call
from Thelma. Will you accept?</i>

631
00:38:03.280 --> 00:38:04.907
Why, yes, I will, operator.

632
00:38:07.326 --> 00:38:09.745
Thelma, where in the Sam Hill are you?

633
00:38:09.829 --> 00:38:13.124
Um, I'm, uh, with Louise.

634
00:38:13.207 --> 00:38:16.043
We're, uh...
We're in the mountains. We're fishin'.

635
00:38:16.127 --> 00:38:18.712
Have you lost your mind? Is that it?

636
00:38:18.796 --> 00:38:22.007
Now, I leave for work, and you
take complete leave of your senses?

637
00:38:22.091 --> 00:38:25.386
<i>(Sighs)</i> Darryl, calm down, please.

638
00:38:25.469 --> 00:38:27.721
Don't get so mad. I can explain, okay?

639
00:38:28.931 --> 00:38:31.559
- See, Louise, uh...
- Hold on! Hold on!

640
00:38:31.642 --> 00:38:34.603
- <i>(Thelma continues, indistinct)</i>
- Oh, come on, Kurt, pick it.

641
00:38:34.687 --> 00:38:36.856
- <i>(Announcer)</i> <i>Kurt knocks the ball loose.</i>
- Pick it!

642
00:38:36.939 --> 00:38:38.357
<i>- Chad Williams's got it.</i>
- Shit! God!

643
00:38:38.441 --> 00:38:41.485
<i>- We end up with the ball...</i>
- <i>(Thelma continues, indistinct)</i>

644
00:38:41.569 --> 00:38:42.570
Christ.

645
00:38:42.653 --> 00:38:46.282
We're just gonna stay there and,
you know, fish and hang out and stuff.

646
00:38:46.365 --> 00:38:48.868
We'll just be gone one more day.
We'll be home tomorrow night.

647
00:38:48.951 --> 00:38:51.287
No, you won't. You'll be back today.

648
00:38:52.288 --> 00:38:54.915
You get your butt back here, Thelma, now.

649
00:38:54.999 --> 00:38:56.167
Goddamn it!

650
00:38:57.501 --> 00:38:58.502
Darryl.

651
00:39:01.464 --> 00:39:05.092
Darryl, you're my husband, not my father.

652
00:39:05.176 --> 00:39:07.219
Oh, now, that does it.

653
00:39:07.303 --> 00:39:09.555
That Louise is nothin'
but a bad influence.

654
00:39:10.431 --> 00:39:12.725
If you're not back here by tonight...

655
00:39:15.603 --> 00:39:16.604
Thelma,

656
00:39:18.397 --> 00:39:21.150
well, then I just don't wanna say.

657
00:39:23.360 --> 00:39:24.361
Darryl.

658
00:39:25.321 --> 00:39:26.322
Thelma.

659
00:39:27.364 --> 00:39:29.116
Go fuck yourself.

660
00:39:29.200 --> 00:39:30.201
<i>(Receiver hangs up)</i>

661
00:39:30.284 --> 00:39:31.619
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

662
00:39:33.037 --> 00:39:35.206
Oh, that's good. That's just sweet.

663
00:39:39.752 --> 00:39:40.878
- Shit! <i>(Chuckles)</i>
- Sorry.

664
00:39:40.961 --> 00:39:42.546
- Darling, you all right?
- Yeah.

665
00:39:42.630 --> 00:39:45.007
- Are you okay? Did I cause that?
- No, I'm sorry.

666
00:39:45.090 --> 00:39:46.926
- No? You're okay?
- Uh-huh.

667
00:39:47.009 --> 00:39:49.220
All right.
Is there something I can do for you?

668
00:39:49.303 --> 00:39:50.763
- No, it's okay.
- Hmm?

669
00:39:55.100 --> 00:39:58.395
<i>(Sighs)</i> Crazy.

670
00:40:03.317 --> 00:40:04.527
<i>(Sniffles)</i>

671
00:40:08.614 --> 00:40:09.865
<i>(Sighs)</i>

672
00:40:41.230 --> 00:40:42.273
Excuse me, ma'am.

673
00:40:42.356 --> 00:40:44.316
Uh, may I ask
which direction you're heading?

674
00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:47.778
See, I'm trying to get back to school,
my ride fell through,

675
00:40:47.861 --> 00:40:50.281
and, well, I'm kind of stuck here
like stink on stink.

676
00:40:50.364 --> 00:40:52.283
So I was thinkin' that, uh,

677
00:40:52.366 --> 00:40:55.619
if you're goin' my way
or if I'm going your way...

678
00:40:55.703 --> 00:40:58.247
- I think we're going to Oklahoma City...
- Perfect.

679
00:40:58.330 --> 00:40:59.456
...but I'm not sure.

680
00:40:59.540 --> 00:41:02.126
Yeah, well, I'd appreciate it much.

681
00:41:02.209 --> 00:41:03.836
Um...

682
00:41:03.919 --> 00:41:08.632
Well, see, it's really not up to me.
It's not my car. Um...

683
00:41:08.716 --> 00:41:10.301
We'd have to ask my friend.

684
00:41:11.343 --> 00:41:14.680
But I... She would probably say no.
She's a little bit uptight.

685
00:41:14.763 --> 00:41:16.765
Maybe it's not such a good idea.

686
00:41:16.849 --> 00:41:19.310
But I tell you what.
I thank you for your time.

687
00:41:19.393 --> 00:41:22.229
But, I mean, I can ask, you know.
It wouldn't hurt nothing.

688
00:41:22.855 --> 00:41:24.648
Well, no, it wouldn't hurt.

689
00:41:25.691 --> 00:41:26.692
Hey.

690
00:41:28.152 --> 00:41:30.237
Louise. Hey, Louise.

691
00:41:30.321 --> 00:41:32.615
Uh, this young man here
is on his way back to school,

692
00:41:32.698 --> 00:41:35.284
and I thought since
we're going the same direction,

693
00:41:35.367 --> 00:41:37.745
you know, we could give him a ride, huh?

694
00:41:41.498 --> 00:41:43.250
It's probably not a good idea.

695
00:41:45.252 --> 00:41:46.670
- <i>(Thelma)</i> Louise.
- No, probably not.

696
00:41:46.754 --> 00:41:47.880
But I appreciate your time.

697
00:41:47.963 --> 00:41:50.424
You all have a good day, all right?
Drive safe.

698
00:41:50.507 --> 00:41:51.842
Louise?

699
00:41:52.885 --> 00:41:54.094
<i>(Door opens)</i>

700
00:41:55.679 --> 00:41:56.889
<i>(Door closes)</i>

701
00:41:56.972 --> 00:41:58.057
<i>(Engine starts)</i>

702
00:41:58.140 --> 00:42:00.559
Did you see how polite he is?
He was real sweet.

703
00:42:00.643 --> 00:42:02.311
- Thelma.
- What?

704
00:42:03.646 --> 00:42:06.732
- <i>(Tires screech)</i>
- Hey, cheer up, now. All right?

705
00:42:08.651 --> 00:42:10.944
- <i>(Horn honks)</i>
- <i>(Tires screech)</i>

706
00:42:14.031 --> 00:42:15.658
<i>(Tires screech)</i>

707
00:42:17.326 --> 00:42:18.494
<i>(Louise)</i> Fill her up.

708
00:42:19.328 --> 00:42:21.330
<i>(Thelma)</i> Sure wish we could have
brought him with us.

709
00:42:22.790 --> 00:42:24.375
What'd Darryl have to say?

710
00:42:25.584 --> 00:42:29.838
Oh, he said, "Okay, Thelma, I just wanted
to make sure you was all right.

711
00:42:29.922 --> 00:42:31.757
I sure hope you're havin' fun.
You deserve it.

712
00:42:31.840 --> 00:42:33.884
After all, you put up with me.

713
00:42:33.967 --> 00:42:35.260
I love you, honey."

714
00:42:39.056 --> 00:42:40.349
<i>(Exhales)</i>

715
00:42:41.725 --> 00:42:44.895
So, how long
before we're in goddamn Mexico?

716
00:43:06.375 --> 00:43:08.961
<i>(Thelma)</i> I just didn't think it would hurt
to give somebody a ride.

717
00:43:09.837 --> 00:43:11.171
Did you see his butt?

718
00:43:12.673 --> 00:43:14.633
Darryl don't have a cute butt.

719
00:43:14.717 --> 00:43:16.844
You could park a car
in the shadow of his ass.

720
00:43:16.927 --> 00:43:18.137
<i>(Train crossing bell clanging)</i>

721
00:43:18.220 --> 00:43:20.973
<i>(Louise)</i> I'm sorry. I'm just not
in the mood for company right now.

722
00:43:24.935 --> 00:43:26.311
Here. Take this map.

723
00:43:26.395 --> 00:43:30.649
I need you to find all the secondary roads
to Mexico from Oklahoma City.

724
00:43:30.733 --> 00:43:33.235
I think we should stay off the interstate.
We're too conspicuous.

725
00:43:33.318 --> 00:43:34.528
<i>(Train horn blaring)</i>

726
00:43:34.611 --> 00:43:39.074
Uh, looks like we could get
on this Road 81 here

727
00:43:39.158 --> 00:43:40.617
and head down towards Dallas.

728
00:43:40.701 --> 00:43:41.994
I don't want to go through Texas.

729
00:43:42.077 --> 00:43:43.912
Find some way we don't have to
go through there.

730
00:43:46.623 --> 00:43:49.209
Wait. What?

731
00:43:50.210 --> 00:43:54.548
You want to go to Mexico from Oklahoma,
but you don't wanna go through Texas?

732
00:43:54.631 --> 00:43:58.719
Thelma, you know how I feel about Texas!
We're not goin' that way!

733
00:43:58.802 --> 00:44:01.597
Yeah, I know, Louise,
but we're running for our lives.

734
00:44:01.680 --> 00:44:03.432
I mean, can't you make an exception?

735
00:44:03.515 --> 00:44:05.601
I mean, look at this map!

736
00:44:05.684 --> 00:44:09.688
The only thing between
Oklahoma and Mexico is Texas. Look!

737
00:44:09.772 --> 00:44:11.523
Thelma, I'm not gonna talk about this!

738
00:44:11.607 --> 00:44:14.943
Now, you either find another way
or give me the goddamn map and I will!

739
00:44:15.027 --> 00:44:18.280
- You understand?
- No, Louise, I don't.

740
00:44:18.363 --> 00:44:21.033
Now, how come you never told me
what happened to you there?

741
00:44:26.705 --> 00:44:30.626
Look, you shoot off a guy's head
with his pants down,

742
00:44:30.709 --> 00:44:33.295
believe me, Texas is not the place
you wanna get caught.

743
00:44:33.962 --> 00:44:35.130
Now, trust me.

744
00:44:35.839 --> 00:44:38.425
I told you,
I'm not gonna talk about this anymore.

745
00:44:44.723 --> 00:44:46.767
<i>(Doorbell rings)</i>

746
00:45:16.713 --> 00:45:18.298
Happy birthday, lady.

747
00:45:18.382 --> 00:45:20.884
<i>("The Way You Do The Things You Do"
playing on speakers)</i>

748
00:45:20.968 --> 00:45:23.303
<i>(Thelma, Louise)</i>
<i>♪ You coulda been a cool crook ♪</i>

749
00:45:23.387 --> 00:45:26.139
<i>♪ And, baby, you're so smart ♪</i>

750
00:45:27.349 --> 00:45:30.686
<i>♪ You know you could have been
A schoolbook ♪</i>

751
00:45:30.769 --> 00:45:35.774
<i>♪ Well, you could have been anything
That you wanted to ♪</i>

752
00:45:35.858 --> 00:45:40.487
<i>♪ And I can tell
The way you do the things you do ♪</i>

753
00:45:40.571 --> 00:45:44.366
<i>♪ The way you do the things you do
The way you do the things you do ♪</i>

754
00:45:44.449 --> 00:45:46.285
<i>(Saxophone solo playing)</i>

755
00:45:49.913 --> 00:45:51.164
<i>(Exclaims, chuckles)</i>

756
00:46:01.842 --> 00:46:04.094
- Is the manager in?
- <i>(Patrons chattering)</i>

757
00:46:04.177 --> 00:46:06.638
Marian, there's a police officer here.

758
00:46:06.722 --> 00:46:08.724
<i>(Chattering quiets)</i>

759
00:46:26.533 --> 00:46:29.328
- <i>(Thelma imitates dog whimpering)</i>
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>

760
00:46:29.411 --> 00:46:31.580
All right. All right, Thelma. All right.

761
00:46:31.663 --> 00:46:33.999
- <i>(Imitates dog panting)</i>
- Okay.

762
00:47:05.364 --> 00:47:08.617
The other night there was a murder
out at the Silver Bullet.

763
00:47:09.534 --> 00:47:10.619
A man was shot.

764
00:47:11.912 --> 00:47:17.084
And we have some witnesses
that saw a 1966 T-Bird convertible

765
00:47:17.167 --> 00:47:19.044
leaving the scene,

766
00:47:19.127 --> 00:47:21.630
sort of speeding
out of the driveway there.

767
00:47:21.713 --> 00:47:25.175
And that vehicle is registered
to one Louise Sawyer.

768
00:47:26.510 --> 00:47:31.515
And we have reason to believe your wife
was the other occupant of that car.

769
00:47:33.725 --> 00:47:34.935
What?

770
00:47:38.230 --> 00:47:39.690
What?

771
00:47:39.773 --> 00:47:41.066
What?

772
00:47:41.900 --> 00:47:43.610
<i>(Chuckles)</i> Excuse me.

773
00:47:43.694 --> 00:47:45.195
You're standing in your pizza.

774
00:47:46.613 --> 00:47:48.323
Oh, shit!

775
00:47:48.407 --> 00:47:51.743
So tell me something, Miss Thelma.
How is it you ain't got any kids?

776
00:47:51.827 --> 00:47:55.038
I mean, God gives you somethin' special,
I think you ought to pass it on.

777
00:47:56.331 --> 00:47:59.501
- Well, Darryl... That's my husband.
- Darryl?

778
00:47:59.584 --> 00:48:01.712
Yeah. He says he's not ready yet.

779
00:48:01.795 --> 00:48:04.214
Says he's still too much of a kid himself.

780
00:48:04.297 --> 00:48:06.341
Kind of prides himself on being infantile.

781
00:48:06.425 --> 00:48:07.926
He's got a lot to be proud of.

782
00:48:08.010 --> 00:48:11.013
- Louise and him don't get along.
- <i>(Louise)</i> That's putting it mildly.

783
00:48:11.096 --> 00:48:13.724
- She thinks he's a pig.
- I know he's a pig.

784
00:48:15.267 --> 00:48:17.185
Did you get married real young,
Miss Thelma?

785
00:48:18.228 --> 00:48:21.314
- Well, I guess 18 is kind of young.
- <i>(Truck honks melody)</i>

786
00:48:23.108 --> 00:48:26.903
But we'd already been going out four years
when we got married.

787
00:48:26.987 --> 00:48:29.281
- Uh, how long?
- Four years.

788
00:48:29.364 --> 00:48:31.450
- Hmm.
- I never been with anybody but Darryl.

789
00:48:32.701 --> 00:48:33.952
Oh, I'm sorry.

790
00:48:34.036 --> 00:48:38.665
Well, if you don't mind me saying so,
he sounds like a real asshole.

791
00:48:40.917 --> 00:48:43.962
It's okay. He is an asshole.

792
00:48:44.046 --> 00:48:46.048
Most of the time, I just let it slide.

793
00:48:48.925 --> 00:48:51.595
You better slow down there, Miss Louise.
That's a cop up ahead.

794
00:48:52.262 --> 00:48:53.430
- Shit.
- <i>(Passenger)</i> Yep.

795
00:49:29.674 --> 00:49:32.094
Maybe you got
a few too many parking tickets?

796
00:49:32.969 --> 00:49:35.931
We'll take you to Oklahoma City.
Then you best be on your way, all right?

797
00:49:36.014 --> 00:49:37.015
All right.

798
00:49:44.606 --> 00:49:48.151
Prints on the trunk of the car
match those of Thelma Dickinson.

799
00:49:48.235 --> 00:49:50.570
Well, I'll be damned. Isn't that strange?

800
00:49:50.654 --> 00:49:52.823
And the husband says a gun is missing.

801
00:49:53.740 --> 00:49:55.242
She took a lot of stuff.

802
00:49:56.243 --> 00:49:59.412
It looks like she maybe planned
on being gone a while.

803
00:49:59.496 --> 00:50:04.584
The strange thing is, her husband said
she would never touch that gun.

804
00:50:05.585 --> 00:50:08.421
He got it for her
'cause he's out late a lot,

805
00:50:09.422 --> 00:50:12.759
but he said she'd never touch it,
wouldn't learn to shoot it.

806
00:50:12.843 --> 00:50:14.761
Just kept it in a drawer for years.

807
00:50:14.845 --> 00:50:17.264
- What kind of gun was it?
- .38.

808
00:50:17.347 --> 00:50:18.974
Right. Where are they?

809
00:50:19.057 --> 00:50:23.061
They were on their way to some guy's cabin
and, um, they never showed up.

810
00:50:25.230 --> 00:50:27.941
- <i>(Thunder rumbling)</i>
- All right.

811
00:50:28.024 --> 00:50:31.194
Now, I'm gonna go and... Listen up.
I'm gonna go in. It's gonna take a minute.

812
00:50:31.278 --> 00:50:33.113
You two better say your goodbyes,
you understand?

813
00:50:33.196 --> 00:50:34.406
- <i>(Passenger)</i> All right.
- <i>(Louise)</i> Huh?

814
00:50:34.489 --> 00:50:35.490
Okay.

815
00:50:40.745 --> 00:50:41.580
- Hi.
- Hi.

816
00:50:41.663 --> 00:50:44.875
Um, I'm here to pick up a money order
for Louise Sawyer.

817
00:50:47.961 --> 00:50:49.171
There's nothing.

818
00:50:50.130 --> 00:50:53.800
How about "Peaches"?
Could you try code word "Peaches"?

819
00:50:53.884 --> 00:50:55.969
Did I hear somebody say "Peaches"?

820
00:50:57.429 --> 00:50:58.722
Oh, my God. Jimmy.

821
00:50:58.805 --> 00:51:00.515
That's the secret word.

822
00:51:01.808 --> 00:51:03.476
Show the lady what she's won, Don.

823
00:51:03.560 --> 00:51:04.769
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

824
00:51:06.188 --> 00:51:09.316
- What are you doin' here?
- I just came to see you, baby.

825
00:51:12.319 --> 00:51:15.530
Can I have another room, please?
Put it on my, uh, credit card.

826
00:51:20.493 --> 00:51:21.995
<i>(Both chuckle)</i>

827
00:51:24.623 --> 00:51:27.250
- <i>(Louise)</i> Thelma. Get your foot down.
- <i>(Thelma chuckling)</i>

828
00:51:27.334 --> 00:51:29.127
Look who's here.

829
00:51:29.211 --> 00:51:32.881
- Oh, shit! Jimmy. Hi, stranger.
- <i>(Jimmy)</i> Mmm.

830
00:51:32.964 --> 00:51:34.507
What in the world are you doin' here?

831
00:51:34.591 --> 00:51:37.594
Ask me no questions
and I'll tell you no lies.

832
00:51:37.677 --> 00:51:40.013
Good answer. Same goes double for me.

833
00:51:40.847 --> 00:51:42.140
Who's the cowboy?

834
00:51:42.224 --> 00:51:44.476
- Oh, this here, uh... This is J.D.
- How do?

835
00:51:44.559 --> 00:51:46.019
- He's uh, uh, a student.
- He's gone.

836
00:51:46.102 --> 00:51:49.314
We're just giving him a ride to here,
then he... he...

837
00:51:49.397 --> 00:51:51.858
- Louise said that he would have to go, so...
- <i>(Louise)</i> He's gone.

838
00:51:51.942 --> 00:51:54.486
- ...I guess that's what he's doing.
- Yeah, I reckon that's what I'm doing.

839
00:51:54.569 --> 00:51:56.238
- He's gone.
- <i>(J.D.)</i> Like the wind.

840
00:51:56.321 --> 00:51:57.530
- Have a good trip.
- <i>(Thelma)</i> Okay.

841
00:51:57.614 --> 00:51:58.615
<i>(Louise)</i> Thank you.

842
00:51:58.698 --> 00:52:01.243
- Nice to meet you.
- <i>(Engine starts)</i>

843
00:52:02.077 --> 00:52:04.788
Yep. Yep, that's him goin'.

844
00:52:04.871 --> 00:52:06.373
I love to watch him go.

845
00:52:06.456 --> 00:52:08.333
<i>(Louise)</i> Thelma kind of took to him.

846
00:52:08.416 --> 00:52:10.835
<i>(Jimmy)</i> Yeah, well,
I got you a room there, Thelma.

847
00:52:10.919 --> 00:52:13.713
You can go on in and take yourself
a nice, cold shower.

848
00:52:13.797 --> 00:52:16.758
<i>(Thelma)</i> Well, you know me, Jimmy.
I'm just a wild woman.

849
00:52:23.431 --> 00:52:25.433
<i>(Rain pattering)</i>

850
00:52:29.020 --> 00:52:30.855
<i>(Exhales)</i> It's our future.

851
00:52:40.573 --> 00:52:41.783
What are you gonna tell him?

852
00:52:43.618 --> 00:52:44.661
Nothin'.

853
00:52:45.662 --> 00:52:47.247
I'm not gonna tell him a thing.

854
00:52:48.373 --> 00:52:51.668
Least I can do is not make him any more
of an accessory than he already is.

855
00:52:52.335 --> 00:52:55.505
You are so sweet to that guy.
You know, you really are.

856
00:52:55.588 --> 00:52:57.590
Imagine not wantin' to drag him into this.

857
00:52:57.674 --> 00:52:59.676
I didn't ask him to come.

858
00:52:59.759 --> 00:53:03.596
He's no different than any other guy.
He just loves the chase, is all.

859
00:53:03.680 --> 00:53:07.183
Well, he sure got his work
cut out for him now, don't he?

860
00:53:07.267 --> 00:53:08.977
Thelma, just put a lid on it!

861
00:53:09.060 --> 00:53:11.062
<i>(News anchors chattering on TV)</i>

862
00:53:11.813 --> 00:53:12.814
Now...

863
00:53:14.858 --> 00:53:17.235
I want you to just... You guard that money.

864
00:53:18.153 --> 00:53:19.154
Okay.

865
00:53:19.237 --> 00:53:23.491
And if there's any problem,
then you call me in Room 211.

866
00:53:25.118 --> 00:53:26.286
Okay.

867
00:53:27.454 --> 00:53:28.496
I won't wait up.

868
00:53:28.580 --> 00:53:30.081
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

869
00:53:31.124 --> 00:53:32.751
<i>(Knock on door)</i>

870
00:53:34.085 --> 00:53:36.087
<i>(Rain continues pattering)</i>

871
00:53:46.973 --> 00:53:48.516
- You want a drink?
- No.

872
00:53:50.727 --> 00:53:52.228
Why don't you tell me what's going on?

873
00:53:54.856 --> 00:53:57.025
I'm not gonna tell you what's goin' on.

874
00:53:57.108 --> 00:53:59.069
Someday soon
you'll understand why I can't,

875
00:53:59.152 --> 00:54:01.696
but I'm not goin' to, so don't ask me.

876
00:54:04.949 --> 00:54:07.869
- Can I ask you one thing?
- Maybe.

877
00:54:08.828 --> 00:54:11.289
- You in love with somebody else?
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>

878
00:54:11.373 --> 00:54:13.333
Does this have somethin' to do
with another man?

879
00:54:14.250 --> 00:54:16.252
No, it's not anything like that.

880
00:54:17.962 --> 00:54:21.091
<i>(Clicks tongue)</i>
Well, then what is it, goddamn it?

881
00:54:22.092 --> 00:54:23.968
Are you just gonna leave for fucking ever?

882
00:54:25.887 --> 00:54:28.098
- What, did you fuckin' kill somebody?
- <i>(Table clattering)</i>

883
00:54:28.181 --> 00:54:30.100
You start this shit, I'm out of here.

884
00:54:34.646 --> 00:54:35.980
I'm sorry.

885
00:54:37.816 --> 00:54:40.443
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

886
00:54:40.527 --> 00:54:43.571
<i>(Inhales, sighs)</i> You wanna come back
over there and sit down?

887
00:54:43.655 --> 00:54:45.573
I wanna give you somethin'.

888
00:54:45.657 --> 00:54:47.033
I'm fine right here.

889
00:54:47.117 --> 00:54:49.536
- I wanna give you somethin'.
- Give it to me here.

890
00:54:54.958 --> 00:54:56.251
Here.

891
00:55:06.428 --> 00:55:09.472
<i>(Chuckles)</i>
Why don't you try it on? <i>(Sighs)</i>

892
00:55:11.224 --> 00:55:14.352
<i>(Clicks tongue)</i> Well, you didn't see
that one comin', did you?

893
00:55:16.229 --> 00:55:17.564
Why, Jimmy?

894
00:55:20.233 --> 00:55:21.443
Why now?

895
00:55:23.319 --> 00:55:25.530
Try not to get too excited, Louise.

896
00:55:25.613 --> 00:55:30.618
I just flew across two states
with that ring in my fuckin' hand and, uh...

897
00:55:32.245 --> 00:55:34.664
Uh... <i>(Sighs)</i> You know I hate to fly.

898
00:55:37.083 --> 00:55:39.377
You came all this way
because you thought...

899
00:55:39.461 --> 00:55:41.588
you thought I was with somebody else.

900
00:55:44.215 --> 00:55:45.967
No, that's not why I came.

901
00:55:49.846 --> 00:55:53.349
Because, uh, you know, I...
I don't want to lose you.

902
00:55:53.433 --> 00:55:57.020
And I get the feeling like
you're gonna, like, split permanently.

903
00:55:57.103 --> 00:55:58.980
That's not a good reason to get married.

904
00:56:01.399 --> 00:56:02.984
Well, I thought that's what you wanted.

905
00:56:04.652 --> 00:56:05.862
I did.

906
00:56:07.530 --> 00:56:09.115
But not like this.

907
00:56:09.199 --> 00:56:11.868
<i>(Reporter on TV)</i> <i>... cooking methods.
Questions are encouraged.</i>

908
00:56:11.951 --> 00:56:13.870
<i>- The Fort Reno Days Festival highlights...</i>
- <i>(Knocking)</i>

909
00:56:13.953 --> 00:56:17.123
<i>...settler, Indian
and military lifestyles of years past.</i>

910
00:56:17.207 --> 00:56:20.293
<i>And the military contingent boasts
an actual member of the 5th Cavalry.</i>

911
00:56:20.376 --> 00:56:22.962
- Louise?
- <i>(J.D.)</i> No, Thelma, it's me.

912
00:56:24.422 --> 00:56:26.090
- Surprise.
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>

913
00:56:27.175 --> 00:56:30.094
I was just out there
and I was thinkin' that, uh...

914
00:56:30.178 --> 00:56:32.639
Well, I know I'm supposed to be gone
and all, but...

915
00:56:33.932 --> 00:56:34.933
You know.

916
00:56:38.728 --> 00:56:41.689
And I'm not havin' a turd's luck
getting a ride out in this rain.

917
00:56:43.149 --> 00:56:44.984
I was just thinkin' about you.

918
00:56:49.781 --> 00:56:51.699
Uh, this... this is crazy. This... I'm...

919
00:56:51.783 --> 00:56:54.494
I'm gonna get out of your hair.
All right? I'm gonna...

920
00:56:55.078 --> 00:56:57.539
Well, wait, wait.

921
00:56:58.706 --> 00:56:59.916
Where you goin'?

922
00:57:03.253 --> 00:57:06.631
Ah, I don't know. You know. Nowhere.

923
00:57:06.714 --> 00:57:10.426
You think I'm happy playin'
my one-night gigs in Ramada Inn lounges?

924
00:57:10.510 --> 00:57:12.929
You think you're the only one
with dreams that didn't work out?

925
00:57:13.012 --> 00:57:14.973
We both got what we settled for.

926
00:57:15.848 --> 00:57:17.725
I think maybe
you just don't love me anymore.

927
00:57:18.309 --> 00:57:19.686
No, I do love you.

928
00:57:24.315 --> 00:57:26.526
But I think it's time to just...

929
00:57:29.028 --> 00:57:30.989
let go of the old mistakes.

930
00:57:33.199 --> 00:57:34.951
Just chalk it up to...

931
00:57:36.995 --> 00:57:38.705
bad timin'.

932
00:57:40.665 --> 00:57:42.667
I think it's time to let go.

933
00:57:44.877 --> 00:57:46.879
- <i>(J.D.)</i> Look out. Look out.
- Don't... Don't do it.

934
00:57:46.963 --> 00:57:50.550
- <i>(Thelma exclaims)</i> Ow!
- Oh! Oh! Oh! Come on.

935
00:57:50.633 --> 00:57:52.427
- What are you doing?
- You're too... Come on. Here.

936
00:57:52.510 --> 00:57:54.762
- All right, all right. I'll do it.
- Your turn.

937
00:57:54.846 --> 00:57:56.306
- <i>(Thelma)</i> Oh, shit. Here we go.
- Come on.

938
00:57:56.389 --> 00:57:57.223
<i>(Hands slap)</i>

939
00:57:57.307 --> 00:57:59.559
- Well, don't just leave 'em there.
- Come on.

940
00:57:59.642 --> 00:58:00.727
- All right.
- <i>(Hands slap)</i>

941
00:58:02.020 --> 00:58:04.355
- Ow! God. What are you...
- <i>(Thelma chuckles)</i>

942
00:58:04.439 --> 00:58:10.111
Aw, you see, this is an unfair advantage.
You got too much metal goin' here.

943
00:58:10.194 --> 00:58:13.489
You wanna lighten the load a little bit?
Yeah?

944
00:58:15.617 --> 00:58:16.993
Yeah.

945
00:58:17.076 --> 00:58:18.870
I think that's better. What do you think?

946
00:58:19.829 --> 00:58:21.497
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah.

947
00:58:23.041 --> 00:58:24.042
<i>(Grunts)</i>

948
00:58:24.125 --> 00:58:26.085
- Take me, break me, make me a man!
- You're gonna hit your head!

949
00:58:26.169 --> 00:58:29.130
- <i>(Laughs)</i> Watch your head! Careful.
- Oh, my head's fine.

950
00:58:29.213 --> 00:58:31.215
Who are you, anyway?

951
00:58:31.299 --> 00:58:36.262
<i>(Groans)</i> I'm the great and powerful Oz.
Who do you want to be?

952
00:58:36.346 --> 00:58:39.766
Come on, tell me.
I know you're not just some schoolboy.

953
00:58:39.849 --> 00:58:43.144
- Nobody ever tells me shit. Tell me.
- Oh, I'm just some guy.

954
00:58:43.227 --> 00:58:47.523
A guy whose parole officer is probably
havin' a shit fit right about now.

955
00:58:47.607 --> 00:58:49.484
What do you mean, parole officer?

956
00:58:50.568 --> 00:58:52.195
Wh... Are you a criminal?

957
00:58:52.278 --> 00:58:54.530
No. No, not no more, Thelma.

958
00:58:54.614 --> 00:58:56.699
Uh, let's see.

959
00:58:56.783 --> 00:58:59.035
Besides bustin' parole,
I haven't done one wrong thing.

960
00:59:00.036 --> 00:59:02.872
- What did you do?
- I'm a robber.

961
00:59:03.915 --> 00:59:09.170
- You're a bank robber?
- No. No. I don't rob no banks. Come on.

962
00:59:09.253 --> 00:59:10.546
What did you rob?

963
00:59:11.923 --> 00:59:15.051
Hmm. Well, let's see.

964
00:59:15.885 --> 00:59:16.969
Let's add it up here.

965
00:59:17.053 --> 00:59:20.640
I, uh, robbed a gas station,

966
00:59:20.723 --> 00:59:24.268
a couple of convenience stores,
liquor stores.

967
00:59:25.395 --> 00:59:27.230
Oh, my God. <i>(Chuckles)</i>

968
00:59:28.773 --> 00:59:29.899
How?

969
00:59:31.776 --> 00:59:34.862
- Come on.
- Okay.

970
00:59:34.946 --> 00:59:37.240
- First you pick your place, all right?
- Mm-hmm.

971
00:59:37.323 --> 00:59:39.617
Then I just sit back
and watch it for a little while,

972
00:59:39.701 --> 00:59:42.286
wait for that right moment
to make my move, see?

973
00:59:42.370 --> 00:59:45.623
That's somethin' you gotta know up here.
That shit cannot be taught.

974
00:59:45.707 --> 00:59:47.583
- Oh. Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, then, uh...

975
00:59:48.584 --> 00:59:51.921
- Oh, shit, I don't wanna talk about this.
- Come on. I do.

976
00:59:53.840 --> 00:59:54.966
All right.

977
00:59:55.675 --> 01:00:00.888
Then I'd waltz right in. Yeah.

978
01:00:00.972 --> 01:00:04.892
And I'd just kind of waltz on in
and I'd say, "Ladies, gentlemen,

979
01:00:04.976 --> 01:00:06.936
let's see who wins a prize
for keepin' their cool.

980
01:00:07.019 --> 01:00:09.605
Simon says, 'Everybody down on the floor.'

981
01:00:09.689 --> 01:00:12.608
Now, nobody loses their head,
then nobody loses their head.

982
01:00:12.692 --> 01:00:16.279
Uh, you, sir. Yeah, you do the honors.

983
01:00:16.362 --> 01:00:18.364
Take that cash,
you put it in that bag right there,

984
01:00:18.448 --> 01:00:20.408
you got an amazing story
to tell your friends.

985
01:00:20.491 --> 01:00:23.494
If not, well, you got a tag on your toe.
You decide."

986
01:00:24.829 --> 01:00:26.080
Simple as that.

987
01:00:27.373 --> 01:00:29.125
Then I just slip on out

988
01:00:30.376 --> 01:00:34.005
and, uh, get the hell out of Dodge, yeah.

989
01:00:35.757 --> 01:00:37.300
- Mm-hmm.
- My goodness.

990
01:00:37.383 --> 01:00:39.761
You were sure gentlemanly about it.

991
01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:42.680
Well, now, I've always believed that,
done properly,

992
01:00:42.764 --> 01:00:45.975
armed robbery doesn't have to be
a totally unpleasant experience.

993
01:00:47.602 --> 01:00:49.145
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>
- What?

994
01:00:49.228 --> 01:00:51.606
You're a real live outlaw, aren't you?

995
01:00:51.689 --> 01:00:56.152
Well, I may be an outlaw, darlin',
but, uh, you're the one stealin' my heart.

996
01:00:56.986 --> 01:00:59.947
- Oh, smooth.
- Oh, yeah. Ooh.

997
01:01:00.031 --> 01:01:02.033
- Isn't he? Isn't he?
- Oh, you're smooth.

998
01:01:02.116 --> 01:01:05.161
- That's right.
- Yeah. How did you get that way? <i>(Laughs)</i>

999
01:01:05.244 --> 01:01:07.163
- All for you.
- Mmm.

1000
01:01:11.959 --> 01:01:14.128
- <i>(Jimmy clicks tongue)</i>
- Remember when we first met?

1001
01:01:16.297 --> 01:01:17.507
Yeah.

1002
01:01:18.883 --> 01:01:20.927
What happened? Tell me what you said.

1003
01:01:21.010 --> 01:01:23.012
I said you had a nice pair of eyes.

1004
01:01:25.723 --> 01:01:28.392
And what'd I say? You remember?

1005
01:01:31.813 --> 01:01:35.817
Yeah, you shut 'em.
Asked me if I knew what color they were.

1006
01:01:37.777 --> 01:01:39.612
And what did you say?

1007
01:01:39.695 --> 01:01:42.532
<i>(Chuckles)</i> I didn't know.

1008
01:01:47.662 --> 01:01:49.455
Jimmy, what color are my eyes?

1009
01:01:52.625 --> 01:01:54.585
<i>(Chuckles)</i> They're brown.

1010
01:02:05.638 --> 01:02:07.640
<i>("Kick the Stones" playing)</i>

1011
01:02:25.116 --> 01:02:26.492
<i>(Thelma exhales)</i>

1012
01:02:26.576 --> 01:02:28.578
<i>(Both breathing heavily)</i>

1013
01:02:29.745 --> 01:02:32.915
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh... ♪</i>

1014
01:02:36.002 --> 01:02:38.796
<i>(Thelma)</i> Wait. <i>(Sighs)</i> Wait.

1015
01:02:38.880 --> 01:02:41.424
<i>♪ Night upon the rocks ♪</i>

1016
01:02:41.507 --> 01:02:46.470
<i>♪ I'm over by the roadhouse
With them rusted engine blocks ♪</i>

1017
01:02:46.554 --> 01:02:51.017
<i>♪ A ghost town with a goldmine
A pickax in my head ♪</i>

1018
01:02:51.100 --> 01:02:56.981
<i>♪ I'm beggin', Mama, please move over
Kick them stones out of my bed ♪</i>

1019
01:02:57.064 --> 01:02:59.442
- <i>(J.D. breathing heavily)</i>
- <i>(Moans)</i>

1020
01:02:59.525 --> 01:03:01.152
<i>(Grunts, chuckles)</i>

1021
01:03:01.235 --> 01:03:04.572
- <i>(Song continues playing)</i>
- <i>(Objects clatter)</i>

1022
01:03:04.655 --> 01:03:06.407
<i>(Thelma moaning)</i>

1023
01:03:07.158 --> 01:03:12.246
<i>♪ I met my sister Sandra
With them jewels and the cross ♪</i>

1024
01:03:12.330 --> 01:03:16.751
<i>♪ Eyes on my lever now
She paint with chili sauce ♪</i>

1025
01:03:16.834 --> 01:03:21.714
<i>♪ I cannot do no business
With your candle lit in red ♪</i>

1026
01:03:21.797 --> 01:03:27.094
<i>♪ I'm beggin', Mama, please move over
Kick them stones out of my bed ♪</i>

1027
01:03:27.178 --> 01:03:31.891
<i>♪ Kick them stones out of my bed
All them stones out of my bed ♪</i>

1028
01:03:43.986 --> 01:03:46.739
<i>("I Can't Untie You From Me" playing)</i>

1029
01:03:48.950 --> 01:03:51.953
<i>♪ Oh, oh ♪</i>

1030
01:03:56.290 --> 01:03:58.084
<i>♪ Baby, baby, baby ♪</i>

1031
01:04:04.590 --> 01:04:06.634
<i>(Song continues playing)</i>

1032
01:04:08.511 --> 01:04:09.887
Y'all want some more coffee?

1033
01:04:11.389 --> 01:04:12.390
Thank you.

1034
01:04:15.309 --> 01:04:18.104
- Anything else?
- <i>(Sniffles)</i>

1035
01:04:21.941 --> 01:04:23.693
Look, I don't know
what's goin' on with you,

1036
01:04:23.776 --> 01:04:27.238
or what happened or what y'all did, but...

1037
01:04:28.990 --> 01:04:33.369
I'm not gonna tell anybody anything,
and I'm not gonna say that I even saw you.

1038
01:04:35.830 --> 01:04:37.915
Okay? <i>(Chuckles)</i>

1039
01:04:37.999 --> 01:04:40.209
Damn, Jimmy, what did you do,
take some kind of pill,

1040
01:04:40.292 --> 01:04:42.169
makes you say all the right stuff?

1041
01:04:42.253 --> 01:04:43.713
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

1042
01:04:45.214 --> 01:04:48.092
Yeah, I'm chokin' on it.

1043
01:04:50.636 --> 01:04:54.140
Uh, you sure you don't want me
to go with you?

1044
01:04:56.183 --> 01:04:59.020
I think it's probably not
a real good idea right now.

1045
01:04:59.979 --> 01:05:04.900
But I'll, um, catch up with you later
on down the road.

1046
01:05:07.111 --> 01:05:08.362
Yeah.

1047
01:05:12.783 --> 01:05:16.704
Well... <i>(Sighs)</i>... my taxi is here.

1048
01:05:20.833 --> 01:05:24.128
So, uh, why don't you just keep that?

1049
01:05:26.047 --> 01:05:28.174
- Okay?
- Thanks.

1050
01:05:30.051 --> 01:05:32.470
<i>(Jimmy)</i> I just want you to be happy.

1051
01:05:33.304 --> 01:05:36.766
I am happy, sweetie. Happy as I can be.

1052
01:05:39.602 --> 01:05:41.020
All right. <i>(Sighs)</i>

1053
01:05:41.103 --> 01:05:43.481
- <i>(Both chuckle)</i>
- All right.

1054
01:05:44.523 --> 01:05:47.568
Well, why don't you give ol' Jimmy
a kiss goodbye?

1055
01:05:48.360 --> 01:05:51.072
And, uh, I'll be gettin' out of here.

1056
01:05:54.950 --> 01:05:57.703
- Come here, ol' Jimmy.
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>

1057
01:05:57.787 --> 01:06:00.289
<i>♪ For the truth in your heart ♪</i>

1058
01:06:00.372 --> 01:06:04.794
<i>♪ Is never, never
Never, never far away ♪</i>

1059
01:06:05.920 --> 01:06:07.213
<i>♪ Oh, baby ♪</i>

1060
01:06:08.422 --> 01:06:11.050
<i>♪ Always, always ♪</i>

1061
01:06:13.636 --> 01:06:17.681
<i>♪ And I've walked a thousand miles ♪</i>

1062
01:06:18.891 --> 01:06:22.770
<i>♪ To the edge of every sea ♪</i>

1063
01:06:22.853 --> 01:06:24.313
<i>(Sighs)</i>

1064
01:06:24.396 --> 01:06:28.150
<i>♪ And I've tried
Oh, yes, I've tried ♪</i>

1065
01:06:28.234 --> 01:06:30.736
<i>(Clicks tongue, chuckles)</i>

1066
01:06:31.779 --> 01:06:34.156
- I'll be seeing you, Louise.
- Mm-hmm.

1067
01:06:39.703 --> 01:06:41.372
You have a safe trip.

1068
01:06:42.248 --> 01:06:44.834
<i>♪ Your name is on the water ♪</i>

1069
01:06:45.960 --> 01:06:46.961
<i>(Chattering)</i>

1070
01:06:47.044 --> 01:06:52.508
<i>♪ And it's written
On the deep blue waves ♪</i>

1071
01:06:52.591 --> 01:06:55.886
<i>♪ In the sky where eagles wander ♪</i>

1072
01:06:55.970 --> 01:06:58.264
It's a good thing he left when he did.

1073
01:06:58.347 --> 01:07:02.268
We thought we were gonna have to
put out a fire. <i>(Laughing)</i>

1074
01:07:05.396 --> 01:07:07.398
<i>(Customers chattering)</i>

1075
01:07:13.654 --> 01:07:15.406
Hi.

1076
01:07:15.489 --> 01:07:19.660
- What happened to your hair?
- Nothin'. Got messed up.

1077
01:07:21.453 --> 01:07:22.872
Thelma, what's wrong with you?

1078
01:07:24.039 --> 01:07:27.710
Nothin'. Why? Do I seem different?

1079
01:07:29.378 --> 01:07:31.088
Well, now that you mention it, yeah.

1080
01:07:31.172 --> 01:07:34.216
You seem like you're crazy
or you're on drugs.

1081
01:07:34.300 --> 01:07:35.676
<i>(Sighs)</i>

1082
01:07:35.759 --> 01:07:39.847
Well, I'm not on drugs,
but I might be crazy!

1083
01:07:39.930 --> 01:07:41.599
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

1084
01:07:45.269 --> 01:07:46.854
Thelma, what happened?

1085
01:07:48.272 --> 01:07:50.107
<i>(Screams, laughs)</i>

1086
01:07:50.191 --> 01:07:52.026
- What happened?
- J.D. came back.

1087
01:07:52.109 --> 01:07:53.944
- <i>(Gasps)</i> Oh, my God, Louise. Oh, my God.
- No.

1088
01:07:54.028 --> 01:07:55.446
- Oh, no!
- I can't believe it.

1089
01:07:55.529 --> 01:07:57.907
- I mean, I just can't believe it!
- No!

1090
01:07:57.990 --> 01:08:01.785
Oh, my God, it's like...
<i>(Gasps, grunts, chuckles)</i>

1091
01:08:01.869 --> 01:08:03.954
I finally understand
what all the fuss is about!

1092
01:08:04.038 --> 01:08:06.874
Now it's just like
a whole 'nother ball game.

1093
01:08:06.957 --> 01:08:10.753
Oh, darlin', I'm so happy for you.
That's great. I really am.

1094
01:08:10.836 --> 01:08:13.130
- Mmm.
- You finally got laid properly.

1095
01:08:13.214 --> 01:08:15.132
- That's so sweet.
- <i>(Both laugh)</i>

1096
01:08:15.216 --> 01:08:16.217
Oh!

1097
01:08:16.300 --> 01:08:19.428
- Where is he now?
- He's takin' a shower.

1098
01:08:21.722 --> 01:08:23.224
Thelma, you left him alone in the room?

1099
01:08:26.810 --> 01:08:29.939
Where's the money?
Oh, my God. Thelma, where's the money?

1100
01:08:30.022 --> 01:08:32.233
It's on the bed table.

1101
01:08:32.316 --> 01:08:33.609
It's okay.

1102
01:08:35.903 --> 01:08:38.781
It's on the nightstand! It's okay.

1103
01:08:42.493 --> 01:08:44.620
<i>(Panting)</i>

1104
01:08:44.703 --> 01:08:47.331
Oh! Oh, goddamn it!

1105
01:08:48.207 --> 01:08:50.668
I've never been lucky! Not one time!

1106
01:08:52.795 --> 01:08:56.173
Shit! That son of a bitch burned me.

1107
01:08:56.257 --> 01:08:59.677
I don't believe it. I don't believe it.

1108
01:09:03.305 --> 01:09:04.723
Louise.

1109
01:09:06.392 --> 01:09:07.601
You okay?

1110
01:09:10.688 --> 01:09:11.897
Louise.

1111
01:09:12.982 --> 01:09:16.485
<i>(Sighs)</i> I'm sorry. I mean it.

1112
01:09:19.238 --> 01:09:21.240
<i>(Breathing heavily)</i>

1113
01:09:22.908 --> 01:09:25.202
Louise, it's okay.

1114
01:09:27.204 --> 01:09:30.916
- It's okay.
- No, Thelma, it's not okay.

1115
01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:32.876
It's definitely not okay.

1116
01:09:35.379 --> 01:09:38.007
None of this is okay.

1117
01:09:38.090 --> 01:09:42.678
I mean, what are we gonna do
for money, huh?

1118
01:09:42.761 --> 01:09:44.930
How we gonna get gas?

1119
01:09:45.014 --> 01:09:48.642
I mean, tradin' on our good looks?
<i>(Laughs, gasps)</i>

1120
01:09:48.726 --> 01:09:50.019
I mean...

1121
01:09:50.769 --> 01:09:54.064
<i>(Sobbing)</i> Oh, goddamn it, Thelma,
it's not okay.

1122
01:09:57.234 --> 01:09:58.736
<i>(Louise wails, continues sobbing)</i>

1123
01:09:58.819 --> 01:10:02.489
Louise. Hey, now you listen to me.

1124
01:10:03.949 --> 01:10:07.703
Don't you worry about it. You hear me?

1125
01:10:07.786 --> 01:10:09.747
Come on. Stand up!

1126
01:10:11.915 --> 01:10:16.295
Louise, just don't you worry about it.
You hear?

1127
01:10:16.378 --> 01:10:17.796
Come on.

1128
01:10:20.549 --> 01:10:22.134
Come on, damn it!

1129
01:10:22.217 --> 01:10:24.303
Get your stuff and let's get out of here.

1130
01:10:25.929 --> 01:10:27.181
Move!

1131
01:10:27.264 --> 01:10:29.933
Jesus Christ, come on. Come on.

1132
01:10:31.643 --> 01:10:35.689
Oh, take your damn time.
Come on. Here we go.

1133
01:10:50.120 --> 01:10:52.122
<i>(Police radio chatter)</i>

1134
01:10:56.835 --> 01:10:59.129
- <i>(Officer groans)</i>
- Damn, damn.

1135
01:10:59.213 --> 01:11:00.756
<i>(Officers laughing)</i>

1136
01:11:02.216 --> 01:11:04.385
<i>(Doorbell rings)</i>

1137
01:11:04.468 --> 01:11:06.387
- Afraid of a little rain, Max?
- <i>(Chuckles)</i>

1138
01:11:06.470 --> 01:11:07.471
Whoo!

1139
01:11:10.974 --> 01:11:13.477
Well, come on in. Wipe your feet.

1140
01:11:26.782 --> 01:11:31.161
As you know, we've tapped your phone
in the event that she calls in.

1141
01:11:31.870 --> 01:11:34.373
Uh, wh... Is that gonna cost me?

1142
01:11:34.456 --> 01:11:35.791
<i>(Max)</i> Uh, excuse me. May I?

1143
01:11:35.874 --> 01:11:39.002
Hey, live it up.
That's what it's there for.

1144
01:11:39.086 --> 01:11:42.464
Uh, we're going to have someone here
at the house on the phones

1145
01:11:42.548 --> 01:11:43.549
until we find them.

1146
01:11:43.632 --> 01:11:44.842
<i>(Whistles)</i>

1147
01:11:44.925 --> 01:11:47.344
The important thing is not to let on
that you know anything.

1148
01:11:47.928 --> 01:11:50.347
- We want to find out where they are.
- Uh-huh.

1149
01:11:50.431 --> 01:11:52.307
I don't want to get too personal,

1150
01:11:53.559 --> 01:11:56.145
but do you have a good relationship
with your wife?

1151
01:11:56.228 --> 01:11:59.398
I... I love Thelma.

1152
01:12:00.691 --> 01:12:04.987
I don't intend anything by that, sir.
It's just a question I have to ask.

1153
01:12:05.070 --> 01:12:08.907
- Are you close with her?
- Yeah. I guess.

1154
01:12:08.991 --> 01:12:13.495
I mean, I'm about as close as I can be
to a nutcase like that.

1155
01:12:13.579 --> 01:12:15.080
<i>(Laughs)</i>

1156
01:12:16.874 --> 01:12:22.087
Uh, yeah, well, if she calls,
just be gentle.

1157
01:12:23.213 --> 01:12:26.592
You know, like you're really happy
to hear from her.

1158
01:12:26.675 --> 01:12:28.719
Like you really miss her.

1159
01:12:28.802 --> 01:12:30.804
Women love that shit.

1160
01:12:32.097 --> 01:12:35.851
<i>(Laughs)</i> Okay. If you say so.

1161
01:12:39.688 --> 01:12:40.814
"Women love that shit."

1162
01:12:40.898 --> 01:12:42.524
- <i>(Laughs)</i>
- <i>(Max)</i> I'm sorry. It's just...

1163
01:12:56.663 --> 01:12:58.790
Oh, cool. Can I wear these?

1164
01:13:06.381 --> 01:13:07.508
Want anything?

1165
01:14:08.443 --> 01:14:12.239
Drive, Louise! Drive! Drive the car!

1166
01:14:13.615 --> 01:14:15.576
<i>(Engine starts)</i>

1167
01:14:17.536 --> 01:14:19.871
Go! Go! Go, go, go, go, go, go!

1168
01:14:23.041 --> 01:14:24.543
What happened?

1169
01:14:25.877 --> 01:14:27.129
You robbed the store?

1170
01:14:27.212 --> 01:14:29.464
- <i>(Screams)</i>
- You robbed the goddamn store?

1171
01:14:29.548 --> 01:14:31.717
- Well, we needed the money.
- Oh!

1172
01:14:31.800 --> 01:14:33.719
It's not like I killed anybody,
for God's sake.

1173
01:14:33.802 --> 01:14:35.345
- Thelma!
- I'm sorry.

1174
01:14:35.429 --> 01:14:37.055
We needed the money. Now we have it.

1175
01:14:37.139 --> 01:14:40.267
Oh, shit! Oh, shit! Oh, shit, Thelma!

1176
01:14:40.350 --> 01:14:41.768
- Louise. Louise.
- Oh, shit!

1177
01:14:41.852 --> 01:14:43.145
- Come on, get a grip.
- Shit!

1178
01:14:43.228 --> 01:14:46.273
- Drive us to goddamn Mexico, will you?
- Okay.

1179
01:14:46.356 --> 01:14:49.234
- Oh, shit! Oh, shit!
- <i>(Exclaims, laughs)</i>

1180
01:14:49.318 --> 01:14:52.988
Well, how... how'd you...
I mean, what did you say?

1181
01:14:53.071 --> 01:14:56.491
Well, I...
I just waltzed on in there and I said...

1182
01:14:56.575 --> 01:14:58.952
<i>Good mornin', ladies and gentlemen.
This is a robbery.</i>

1183
01:14:59.036 --> 01:15:01.622
<i>Now, if nobody loses their head,
nobody will lose their head.</i>

1184
01:15:01.705 --> 01:15:04.625
<i>Simon says, "Y'all lie down on the floor,
please. Right away."</i>

1185
01:15:04.708 --> 01:15:06.793
<i>- You too. Ma'am, would you get down?</i>
- <i>(Customer whimpering)</i>

1186
01:15:06.877 --> 01:15:07.878
<i>Not you, sir.</i>

1187
01:15:07.961 --> 01:15:10.297
<i>Let's see who will win a prize
for keepin' their cool.</i>

1188
01:15:10.380 --> 01:15:11.590
<i>Sir, would you do the honors?</i>

1189
01:15:11.673 --> 01:15:14.343
<i>- Take all the cash, put it in a paper bag.</i>
- <i>(Clerk)</i> <i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

1190
01:15:14.426 --> 01:15:16.845
<i>(Thelma)</i> <i>You're gonna have
an amazing story to tell your friends.</i>

1191
01:15:16.928 --> 01:15:19.348
<i>If not, you'll have a tag on your toe.
You decide.</i>

1192
01:15:20.557 --> 01:15:22.559
- <i>(Bag rustling)</i>
<i>- Hurry up. Let's go.</i>

1193
01:15:23.769 --> 01:15:25.479
<i>Ma'am, would you be quiet?
Sir, get down, please.</i>

1194
01:15:25.562 --> 01:15:29.191
<i>Thank you. Just stay there.
Just get real comfortable.</i>

1195
01:15:30.901 --> 01:15:33.945
<i>Hey, uh, throw in some bottles
of Wild Turkey too, will you?</i>

1196
01:15:34.029 --> 01:15:35.030
<i>(Clerk)</i> <i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

1197
01:15:37.032 --> 01:15:39.284
<i>- Now, you get down too.
- Yes, ma'am.</i>

1198
01:15:39.368 --> 01:15:40.911
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

1199
01:15:40.994 --> 01:15:42.746
<i>I want to thank you all
for your cooperation.</i>

1200
01:15:42.829 --> 01:15:46.041
<i>Now, stay down on the floor till I'm gone.
Have a good day.</i>

1201
01:15:49.127 --> 01:15:50.337
Jesus Christ!

1202
01:15:50.420 --> 01:15:52.130
Good God.

1203
01:15:52.214 --> 01:15:53.382
My Lord.

1204
01:15:53.465 --> 01:15:54.883
<i>("No Lookin' Back" playing)</i>

1205
01:15:54.966 --> 01:15:57.260
<i>♪ I'm fading out of sight ♪</i>

1206
01:15:57.344 --> 01:15:59.680
<i>♪ My wheels are the only sound ♪</i>

1207
01:16:00.555 --> 01:16:03.266
<i>♪ Runnin' at the speed of light ♪</i>

1208
01:16:03.350 --> 01:16:06.603
Hey, Louise, better slow down.

1209
01:16:06.687 --> 01:16:09.564
I'd just die if we get caught
over a speeding ticket.

1210
01:16:09.648 --> 01:16:12.567
You know, for the first time in my life,
I wish this car wasn't green.

1211
01:16:12.651 --> 01:16:14.820
<i>(Song continues playing)</i>

1212
01:16:14.903 --> 01:16:17.531
You sure we should be drivin' like this
in broad daylight?

1213
01:16:17.614 --> 01:16:20.033
No, we shouldn't,
but I want to put some distance between us

1214
01:16:20.117 --> 01:16:22.369
and the scene of our last goddamn crime!

1215
01:16:22.452 --> 01:16:25.080
- Whoo!
- Whoo!

1216
01:16:25.163 --> 01:16:29.876
Whoo! Oh, man!
You wouldn't have believed it.

1217
01:16:29.960 --> 01:16:33.505
It was like I'd been doin' it all my life.
I mean, nobody would believe it.

1218
01:16:35.090 --> 01:16:38.844
- Think you found your callin'?
- Maybe. Maybe.

1219
01:16:38.927 --> 01:16:42.806
- The call of the wild! Whoo!
- Whoo!

1220
01:16:42.889 --> 01:16:45.600
<i>(Cackles)</i> You are disturbed!

1221
01:16:45.684 --> 01:16:48.979
- Yeah, I believe I am.
- Whoo!

1222
01:17:02.492 --> 01:17:04.745
Thelma, don't you litter.

1223
01:17:07.247 --> 01:17:09.082
Wait a minute. Oh, shoot.

1224
01:17:09.166 --> 01:17:11.626
God, I hate when y... This always happens
when you're in a hurry.

1225
01:17:12.627 --> 01:17:13.670
<i>(Bag rustling)</i>

1226
01:17:13.754 --> 01:17:16.298
Damn. What are you gonna do?
Just stay drunk all day?

1227
01:17:18.258 --> 01:17:19.885
- Try to.
- <i>(Scoffs)</i>

1228
01:17:24.723 --> 01:17:26.641
Oh, isn't that nice?

1229
01:17:26.725 --> 01:17:29.561
Truck drivers are always so nice.
Best drivers on the road.

1230
01:17:34.191 --> 01:17:37.652
Oh, Lord. How original.

1231
01:17:43.283 --> 01:17:44.826
<i>(Horn honks)</i>

1232
01:17:45.869 --> 01:17:46.870
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

1233
01:17:46.953 --> 01:17:48.663
- <i>(Horn honks)</i>
- Thank you.

1234
01:17:50.290 --> 01:17:52.292
- Oh!
- Ew, man. That's disgustin'!

1235
01:17:52.375 --> 01:17:54.419
He's a pig! He's a fucking pig!

1236
01:17:54.503 --> 01:17:55.337
That's gross!

1237
01:17:55.420 --> 01:17:58.632
- What's he gotta do that for, anyway?
- I don't know. Huh?

1238
01:17:58.715 --> 01:18:00.509
- They think we like it.
- <i>(Horn honking)</i>

1239
01:18:00.592 --> 01:18:03.094
They think it turns us on or something.

1240
01:18:03.178 --> 01:18:04.262
Shut up!

1241
01:18:04.346 --> 01:18:06.348
<i>(Rain pattering)</i>

1242
01:18:26.201 --> 01:18:27.452
<i>(Car door opens)</i>

1243
01:18:28.870 --> 01:18:30.080
<i>(Door closes)</i>

1244
01:18:42.133 --> 01:18:43.468
James Lennox?

1245
01:18:44.386 --> 01:18:47.013
- Yeah. Who wants to know?
- Arkansas State Police.

1246
01:19:22.340 --> 01:19:23.341
Hi.

1247
01:20:03.048 --> 01:20:04.341
Thelma.

1248
01:20:05.175 --> 01:20:07.594
<i>(Flies buzzing)</i>

1249
01:20:07.677 --> 01:20:10.013
- What?
- I want you to call Darryl.

1250
01:20:11.806 --> 01:20:12.807
What for?

1251
01:20:16.728 --> 01:20:18.063
- I want you to find...
- Huh?

1252
01:20:18.146 --> 01:20:19.814
I want you to find out
if he knows anything.

1253
01:20:19.898 --> 01:20:22.734
If you think he does,
you gotta hang up the phone.

1254
01:20:22.817 --> 01:20:26.571
That means the police have told him,
and the phone's probably tapped.

1255
01:20:26.655 --> 01:20:29.950
Tapped the phone?
What are you talkin' about?

1256
01:20:30.033 --> 01:20:33.078
Come on, Thelma.
Murder one and armed robbery?

1257
01:20:33.161 --> 01:20:34.204
- Murder one?
- Uh-huh.

1258
01:20:34.287 --> 01:20:36.122
- We can't even say it was self-defense?
- It wasn't.

1259
01:20:36.206 --> 01:20:39.250
- We were walkin' away. We got away.
- Yeah, but they don't know that.

1260
01:20:39.334 --> 01:20:40.752
It was just you and me there.

1261
01:20:40.835 --> 01:20:42.587
I'll say he raped me
and you had to shoot him.

1262
01:20:42.671 --> 01:20:44.255
That's almost the truth.

1263
01:20:44.339 --> 01:20:46.633
- It won't work.
- Why not?

1264
01:20:46.716 --> 01:20:49.594
Because there's no physical evidence.
Can't prove he did it.

1265
01:20:49.678 --> 01:20:52.764
We can't even probably prove by now
that he touched you.

1266
01:20:54.224 --> 01:20:55.350
God.

1267
01:20:56.267 --> 01:20:58.395
The law is some tricky shit, isn't it?

1268
01:21:02.774 --> 01:21:04.734
Hey, how do you know
about all this stuff, anyway?

1269
01:21:04.818 --> 01:21:07.612
Besides, what are we gonna say about
the robbery? There's no excuse for that.

1270
01:21:07.696 --> 01:21:10.031
There's no such thing
as justifiable robbery.

1271
01:21:10.115 --> 01:21:12.325
- <i>(Engine starts)</i>
- All right, Louise, will ya!

1272
01:21:12.409 --> 01:21:13.618
Where'd you get this?

1273
01:21:14.494 --> 01:21:15.495
Stole it.

1274
01:21:24.921 --> 01:21:26.923
<i>(People chattering)</i>

1275
01:21:28.008 --> 01:21:29.050
<i>(Darryl)</i> Hi.

1276
01:21:29.801 --> 01:21:32.679
Hi! Huh!

1277
01:21:34.597 --> 01:21:35.890
Who's the nut?

1278
01:21:36.599 --> 01:21:39.144
- That's Mrs. Dickinson's husband.
- Excuse me.

1279
01:21:39.227 --> 01:21:41.604
Well, shit twice and fall back in it.

1280
01:21:42.480 --> 01:21:43.565
God.

1281
01:21:45.483 --> 01:21:48.570
Where'd you get the $6,600 in cash?

1282
01:21:50.697 --> 01:21:52.073
Uh, a friend.

1283
01:21:52.157 --> 01:21:53.742
We spoke with a gentleman today

1284
01:21:53.825 --> 01:21:57.454
who says he delivered very close to
that same amount to a Ms. Louise Sawyer.

1285
01:21:57.537 --> 01:21:59.330
Do you know her too?

1286
01:21:59.414 --> 01:22:01.499
Uh... <i>(Clears throat)</i> Yes, sir.

1287
01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:04.586
Yeah, I believe
she's the woman drivin' the car.

1288
01:22:05.670 --> 01:22:08.965
He said he took it to a motel
in Oklahoma City.

1289
01:22:09.049 --> 01:22:11.342
He also says that, at that time,
he met a man.

1290
01:22:12.260 --> 01:22:15.513
He identified you
through a series of mug shots.

1291
01:22:15.597 --> 01:22:18.725
He also told us
that you and Mrs. Dickinson seemed close.

1292
01:22:19.601 --> 01:22:20.602
Is that true?

1293
01:22:21.686 --> 01:22:23.146
Uh, well, sir,

1294
01:22:24.022 --> 01:22:27.067
you might say we had
a meetin' of the minds, yeah.

1295
01:22:28.526 --> 01:22:30.737
Are you aware
that Mrs. Dickinson and Ms. Sawyer

1296
01:22:30.820 --> 01:22:32.572
are wanted in connection with a murder?

1297
01:22:32.655 --> 01:22:35.492
Murder? What, Thelma? Well, damn!

1298
01:22:35.575 --> 01:22:38.495
Did they ever indicate that they might be
on the run from the law?

1299
01:22:39.370 --> 01:22:42.248
Um, well, you know, sir,
now that you mention it,

1300
01:22:42.332 --> 01:22:43.958
they might have seemed a little bit jumpy.

1301
01:22:45.502 --> 01:22:48.088
- You know what?
- What?

1302
01:22:48.171 --> 01:22:49.881
You're starting to irritate me.

1303
01:22:49.964 --> 01:22:51.424
Yeah, me too.

1304
01:22:51.508 --> 01:22:53.134
Well, that'll happen.

1305
01:22:54.177 --> 01:22:55.887
You two boys have a lot in common.

1306
01:22:55.970 --> 01:22:58.181
Maybe I should just step
out of the room for a sec.

1307
01:23:01.267 --> 01:23:02.685
I got a better idea.

1308
01:23:05.396 --> 01:23:08.191
Do you mind if I speak to him alone
for a minute?

1309
01:23:12.070 --> 01:23:13.071
<i>(Clicks tongue)</i>

1310
01:23:13.696 --> 01:23:17.117
<i>(Door opens, closes)</i>

1311
01:23:18.326 --> 01:23:19.744
Ah...

1312
01:23:21.704 --> 01:23:23.498
<i>(Sighs)</i>

1313
01:23:26.501 --> 01:23:29.337
What? What'd I do? Nothin', that's what.

1314
01:23:29.420 --> 01:23:31.881
Tell you somethin',
this is a crock of shit,

1315
01:23:31.965 --> 01:23:33.758
Mr. John fucking Law.

1316
01:23:41.558 --> 01:23:43.685
Son, I got a feeling about something and...

1317
01:23:43.768 --> 01:23:46.354
- Yeah?
- ...I just wanna ask your opinion.

1318
01:23:48.940 --> 01:23:51.651
Do you think Thelma Dickinson
would have committed armed robbery

1319
01:23:51.734 --> 01:23:53.736
if you hadn't taken all their money?

1320
01:23:56.030 --> 01:23:57.699
Get your foot off that table.

1321
01:24:03.121 --> 01:24:04.497
Cat got your tongue?

1322
01:24:04.581 --> 01:24:06.583
No. No, I...

1323
01:24:06.666 --> 01:24:09.252
Well, how you know I took it?
How you know they didn't...

1324
01:24:11.504 --> 01:24:13.464
Don't you fucking lie to me!

1325
01:24:14.632 --> 01:24:16.885
There's two girls out there
that had a chance.

1326
01:24:16.968 --> 01:24:18.636
They had a chance.

1327
01:24:18.720 --> 01:24:21.014
- And now you've screwed it up for them.
- No.

1328
01:24:21.097 --> 01:24:22.932
And now they're in some serious trouble.

1329
01:24:23.016 --> 01:24:25.185
And I'm gonna hold you
personally responsible

1330
01:24:25.268 --> 01:24:27.395
for at least part of it
if anything happens to them.

1331
01:24:28.271 --> 01:24:30.106
I got no feelin' for you.

1332
01:24:30.190 --> 01:24:33.234
Now, you're either gonna tell me
every damn thing you know,

1333
01:24:33.318 --> 01:24:36.237
so there's a small chance
that I can actually do them some good,

1334
01:24:37.238 --> 01:24:39.157
or I'm gonna be all over you
like a fly on shit

1335
01:24:39.240 --> 01:24:40.992
for the rest of your natural life.

1336
01:24:41.075 --> 01:24:43.870
Your miseries
will be my goddamn mission in life.

1337
01:24:44.454 --> 01:24:45.538
Yes, sir.

1338
01:24:48.082 --> 01:24:50.752
- Okay?
- Yeah. Yeah. That's right.

1339
01:24:50.835 --> 01:24:52.462
- We understand each other?
- Yeah.

1340
01:24:52.545 --> 01:24:53.546
Okay.

1341
01:24:58.176 --> 01:24:59.510
- Mr. Dickinson?
- Yeah?

1342
01:24:59.594 --> 01:25:01.888
If you'd just hang on,
I want a word with you.

1343
01:25:02.931 --> 01:25:04.307
I like your wife.

1344
01:25:06.476 --> 01:25:08.853
- Hey, come back here!
- <i>(Officer)</i> Hey, hey! Whoa!

1345
01:25:08.937 --> 01:25:11.439
Come back here, you little shit! I'll...

1346
01:25:11.522 --> 01:25:13.399
<i>(Exclaims)</i> Come here!

1347
01:25:13.483 --> 01:25:15.818
All right, all right, all right.
Come here! Come here!

1348
01:25:15.902 --> 01:25:17.195
- Come on!
- <i>(Officer)</i> Come on, now.

1349
01:25:17.278 --> 01:25:19.322
- I'll kill him!
- <i>(Officer)</i> Come on, now, Darryl.

1350
01:25:19.405 --> 01:25:20.240
I'll kill you!

1351
01:25:34.879 --> 01:25:36.130
<i>(Bell dings)</i>

1352
01:25:43.304 --> 01:25:44.722
What will it be, ladies?

1353
01:25:44.806 --> 01:25:47.225
Fill her up. There you go.

1354
01:25:47.308 --> 01:25:48.434
Um...

1355
01:25:50.979 --> 01:25:52.563
Excuse me. Do you have a phone?

1356
01:25:55.441 --> 01:25:56.442
Thank you.

1357
01:25:57.318 --> 01:25:59.654
Thelma, listen up, now.
If you even think he knows...

1358
01:25:59.737 --> 01:26:02.657
Even if you're not sure,
I want you to hang up.

1359
01:26:02.740 --> 01:26:04.325
- You understand?
- Yeah.

1360
01:26:11.416 --> 01:26:13.251
<i>("Don't Look Back" playing)</i>

1361
01:26:14.669 --> 01:26:18.256
<i>♪ Goin' in her own good time ♪</i>

1362
01:26:18.339 --> 01:26:21.843
<i>♪ She ain't takin' no airplane ♪</i>

1363
01:26:21.926 --> 01:26:24.846
<i>♪ Don't want to get there too fast ♪</i>

1364
01:26:25.972 --> 01:26:29.559
<i>♪ It's not too late
She can still take it back ♪</i>

1365
01:26:29.642 --> 01:26:31.936
<i>♪ Maybe it all will pass... ♪</i>

1366
01:26:32.020 --> 01:26:33.813
